#*: I have not that '''alacrity''' of spirit
#*: Nor cheer of mind that I was wont to have.
#* {{quote-text|lang=en|year=1837|author={{w|Charles Dickens}}|title=The Pickwick Papers|chapter=12|passage="I'll get into the clothes this minute, if they're here," said Sam, with great '''alacrity'''.}}
